GAUTENG Public Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo has appealed to motorists to drive responsibly. Mamabolo said yesterday high traffic volumes were expected on the road this week as people were returning from holiday. “We’re pleading with road users to be smart drivers and save lives,” he said. Traffic cops would be on high alert to ensure road safety and compliance with traffic laws. Mamabolo said his department believed motorists were to blame for: ) Drunk driving ) Speeding and reckless overtaking ) Failing to fasten seat belts ) Using cellphones while driving ) Overloading and vehicle unroadworthiness ) Aggression and lawlessness. He said the department promoted and encouraged smart driving: that is, taking extra lessons in advanced driving.